H0.text: The amniotic sac is the sac that usually breaks at the start of childbirth.

H1.text: Umbilical is the sac that usually breaks to start childbirth.

H2.text: Uterine is the sac that usually breaks to start childbirth.

H3.text: Protein is the sac that usually breaks to start childbirth.

A4.text: During labor, the amniotic sac must break so that the child can be born.

A5.text: Normally, it occurs spontaneously at full term either during or at the beginning of labor.
